The paper deals with a variant of the classical Bin Packing Problem, which is a well-known problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and lower bounds, which are topics in theoretical computer science and game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm developed in the paper involves repacking a bounded number of items in each time step, which is a combinatorial optimization problem and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses techniques from linear programming and mathematical programming, which are topics in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the asymptotic approximation ratio and lower bound, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
